    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "The current way of building with Cython will result in a shared library in the end, i.e. `.so`, is there a reason for us to build into `.so`?\r\n\r\nI wonder if it could be built into a `.o` or static library file. The benefit of a static library is that we can combine everything into a single executable, instead for shared library we will have the binary loading the separate shared library file.",
    "closed_at": "2019-08-03T06:13:17Z",
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Yes, that possibility exists. You can link multiple extension modules together and use the \"inittab\" mechanism to load them into CPython.\r\nhttps://docs.python.org/3/extending/embedding.html#extending-embedded-python\r\nhttps://docs.python.org/3.5/c-api/import.html#c.PyImport_AppendInittab",
